# Documentation Sync

After **major** changes (new features, CLI commands/flags, runtime behavior, architecture, CI, release scope, or large refactors), update user-facing documentation in the **same PR or session** — do not leave docs stale.

## When this applies

Treat the change as major if it affects any of:

- Language syntax, semantics, or runtime behavior
- CLI commands, flags, or output formats
- Architecture, crate layout, or CI jobs
- Feature status (stable ↔ experimental ↔ planned)
- Roadmap, release scope, or product positioning
- New examples, transports, or integrations (ROS2, FFI, fleet, triggers, etc.)

Small bug fixes, refactors with no user-visible effect, and test-only changes do **not** require doc updates unless CI or contributor workflow changed.

## Required updates (checklist)

Always review these after major work:

| File | Update when |
|------|-------------|
| `README.md` | New capabilities, CLI, examples, differentiators, or roadmap shift |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | Any user-visible addition, fix, or breaking change |
| `docs/feature-status.md` | Stability tier or capability matrix changes |
| `docs/getting-started.md` | New commands, workflows, or demo paths |
| `docs/README.md` | New guides, repo layout, or doc index changes |

Also update topic-specific docs when relevant:

| Change type | Docs to update |
|-------------|----------------|
| Language / syntax | `docs/spanda-language.md`, dedicated guide if one exists (e.g. `docs/triggers.md`) |
| Runtime / compiler | `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/spanda-architecture.md` |
| Concurrency / fleet / triggers | `docs/concurrency.md`, `docs/triggers.md` |
| Hardware / deploy / verify | `docs/hardware-compatibility.md` |
| Packages / registry | `docs/packages.md`, `docs/spanda-toml.md`, `docs/registry.md` |
| FFI / ROS2 / transports | `docs/ffi-and-ecosystem.md` |
| Roadmap / release planning | `docs/roadmap.md`, `docs/product-strategy.md` |
| Contributor workflow | `CONTRIBUTING.md` |
| VS Code / LSP / editor | `editor/vscode/README.md`, `docs/getting-started.md` (LSP section) |

## Workflow

1. Implement the feature and tests.
2. Before finishing, walk the checklist above and update every affected doc.
3. Add or reference a runnable example; link it from `README.md` and/or `docs/getting-started.md` if it is a key demo.
4. Add an `[Unreleased]` entry to `CHANGELOG.md` for user-visible changes.
5. If feature status changed, update `docs/feature-status.md` and `docs/roadmap.md`.

Do **not** consider a major change complete until documentation reflects it.
